            <div type="translation">
                <p>Accept your' s mother prayer, Word. What do you wish mother ? Save the mortals/humans! They angered me. Have mercy my son. But they don't regret. Save them by your grace. They will be saved. Thank you Word.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Damaged. Partially preserved. A cross with dots in the angles marks the beginning of the text. The words δέξαι, αἰτεῖς, σωτηρίαν, ἐπιστρέφουσιν, καί, σῶσον, ἕξουσι are misspelled. Accents and breathings with errors. The depiction of the Virgin is directly related to the depiction of Christ on the south pier. Is essentially a dialogue between Virgin and Christ. Virgin the Merciful addresses Christ pleading him to show mercy to the humankind. This representation goes back to the Comnenian art and can be found also in other churches in Cyprus like Panagia tou Arakos at Lagoudera village.  </p>
            </div>
